title: Zborowice, Lower Silesian Voivodeship
summary: Zborowice [zbɔrɔˈvit͡sɛ] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Wiązów, within Strzelin County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately 3 kilometres (2 mi) south-west of Wiązów, 9 km (6 mi) east of Strzelin, and 38 km (24 mi) south of the regional capital Wrocław.
content:
Zborowice [zbɔrɔˈvit͡sɛ] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Wiązów, within Strzelin County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately 3 kilometres (2 mi) south-west of Wiązów, 9 km (6 mi) east of Strzelin, and 38 km (24 mi) south of the regional capital Wrocław.
